<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1148,1787]" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1148,1174]" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">Type data:</emphasis>
This species was proposed based on ten females and one male collected by Buchwald in Guayaquil, southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[307,403,1184,1210]" name="Ecuador" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[570,794,1184,1211]" pageId="22" pageNumber="253" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref22678" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[653,704,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
the 
<typeStatus box="[845,943,1185,1211]" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">syntypes</typeStatus>
are housed at 
<collectionCode box="[1109,1195,1184,1210]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">AMNH</collectionCode>
and in the 
<collectionCode box="[1324,1387,1185,1211]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="22" pageNumber="253" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
, but they were not found in this latter collection. Instead, there were found 
<typeStatus box="[964,1062,1221,1247]" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">syntypes</typeStatus>
in the 
<collectionCode box="[1145,1231,1221,1247]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">HNHM</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[1289,1361,1221,1247]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">NMW</collectionCode>
, along with two specimens in the 
<collectionCode box="[452,541,1256,1282]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">AMNH</collectionCode>
. One of the 
<typeStatus box="[679,777,1257,1283]" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">syntypes</typeStatus>
(female) housed in this latter collection is here designated the 
<typeStatus box="[196,302,1292,1318]" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen is in good condition and it has the following data label: 
<collectingCountry box="[1149,1242,1292,1318]" name="Ecuador" pageId="22" pageNumber="253">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
Guayaqil 19101 Buchwald [printed]\ 
